summary:
Project Controls Manager with 10+ years of construction management experience in the maritime infrastructure, data centres, and oil & gas industries in various countries: Netherlands, Denmark, Belgium, Egypt and India. 

Holds a B.Sc. in Civil Engineering from Cairo University and a Certificate in Construction Engineering Estimating from Greenville Technical College, SC, United States. Alumnus of the U.S. Department of State merit based scholarship program NESA, and highly commended by the European Construction Institute for the Young Professional of the Year Award 2016. Speaks Arabic and English fluently, and conversant in Dutch.
